Na kena daucaka na tavioka yaca mena (purple cassava) me yacova na Bila ni Naila (Nile perch, se Nile tilapia ena kedra ivakaraitaki) e sega ni dua na nodra veiwekani vakadodonu ena ivakarau vakavanua. Ia, au rawa ni vakamacalataka vakararaba na ituvaki e dau vakayagataki kina na tavioka kei na nodra bula na ika ena Bila ni Naila, ka vakaraitaka kina na nodrau veiwekani ena so na ituvaki.

Na tavioka, na kena yaca vakailavo o Manihot esculenta, e dua na vuana dau teivaki vakawidewide e Viti kei na veiyasai vuravura ka vuku ni katakata, e kilai ni dau vakayagataki me kakana vakavuravura. Na tavioka yaca mena sa dua na mataqali tavioka e kilai ena nona roka mena se damudamu e na nona ucacevata. E vakayagataki vakatabakidua na ucacevata ni tavioka e na kena vakarautaki na madrai tavioka, na kokoda, se vakaviriki me kenai kakanaloto. E talei na tavioka yaca mena ena vuku ni kena roka totoka kei na kena vauvau ni veika e yaga kina e rogo vinaka ena bula vinaka.

Na Bila ni Naila, ena yasana kadua, sai koya na dua na mataqali ika bulabula e vuravura raraba na kena misini ena wai ni wai gaga kei na wai dravuisiga. E kilai levu ena kena vakayagataki vakaukauwa ena iyaya ni qoli kei na kakana ni waitui ena vica na vanua ena vuravura raraba. E bibi na kedra qoli emuri kei na nodra vakatetevi me vaka e dua na ivurevure ni kakana ni porotini.

Ia, na nodrau veiwekani e rawa ni laurai ena itavi ni tavioka me kakana vakavunau. E rawa ni vakayagataki na tavioka me vakarautaki kakana ni ika ena nodra vakatetevi na Bila ni Naila se so tale na mataqali ika ena vale ni vakatetei ika. Na ucacevata ni tavioka, ni sa vakasuasuataki ka vakarautaki vakavinaka, e rawa ni vakayagataki me dua na iwase ni kakana ni ika ni sa vakarubeci kei na so tale na iyaya dau vakayagataki ena nodra vakatetevi na ika, me vaka na soya kei na karare. Oqo e rawa ni vakatauvatani ena kedra qaravi na bula ni ika kei na nodra vakatoroicaketaka me ra rawata na levu ni veivakatoroicaketaki ena nodra tabana ni vakatetei ika. 

Mai na ibalebale e cake, na veiwekani ena macala duadua ena nodrau vakayagataki ena bula ni tamata kei na bula ni veivoli, ka sega ena dua na ivakarau vakailavo se vakabioloji vakadodonu. Sa vakarautaki ga na tavioka me kakana, kei na Bila ni Naila me vaka e dua na ivurevure ni kakana, ia e rawa ni veisemati ena kena vakayagataki na tavioka ena kakana ni ika ena so na ituvaki.

Traditional Fijian clothing, also known as masi or barkcloth, is a significant aspect of iTaukei culture. The barkcloth is made from the inner bark of the paper mulberry tree, which is stripped, soaked, and then beaten into thin sheets. The sheets are then decorated with traditional patterns and designs using natural dyes.

The designs and patterns on the barkcloth often have symbolic meanings that represent various aspects of Fijian culture, such as social status, family lineage, and cultural beliefs. For example, the "masi kesa" is a type of barkcloth that is decorated with intricate geometric patterns and is traditionally worn by high-ranking chiefs and their families.

Traditional Fijian attire is also worn during important cultural events and ceremonies, such as weddings, funerals, and religious festivals. It is a way for the iTaukei people to honor their ancestors, preserve their cultural heritage, and express their identity as indigenous Fijians.

In summary, traditional Fijian attire is a significant aspect of iTaukei culture that represents social status, family lineage, cultural beliefs, and identity. It is a way for the iTaukei people to honor their ancestors and preserve their cultural heritage.

Na virika vatu ki na valenilotu ni bera ni curu e dau vakayacori me ivakaraitaki ni vakarokoroko ki na kalou, yalo, se vu (ancestral spirits) era nanumi ni tiko ena valenilotu se na vanua vakayalo. E rawa ni vakabibitaki talega na veivakarokorokotaki ki na mata ni vanua se na lewe ni vanua era tiko ena vale oya.

Ni vakatabakidua ki na taro, e kilikili mo virika vakayawa sara na vatu sabera ni ko na curu taumada ki na nomu loma ni vale:

1. **Vakarokoroko ki na Yalo ni Vanua:** Na virika ni vatu e rawa ni vakaraitaka na vakarokoroko ki na yalo ni vanua, se na vu ni vanua oya. Oqo e ivakatakilakila ni nomu kerekere ki na veivakalougatataki, vakacegu, kei na maroroi ni bula vinaka ni o curu ki na vale.

3. **Kena iBalebale Vakavanua kei na Vakasama:** Na ivakarau ni bula vakavanua vakaoqo e vukea na vakananumi kei na veivakamaravutaki ni nodra ibalebale vakavanua kei na nodra vakabauta na tamata. Na virika ni vatu e rawa ni vakasamataka na nomu vakaraitaka na yalomalumalumu kei na veidokai ki na veika vakayalo kei na itovo vakavanua ni vanua oya.
   
4. **Veitaqomaki kei na Saubula:** Ena so na ivakavuvuli vakavanua, na virika ni vatu e rawa ni nanumi me kauta mai na veitaqomaki kei na saubula vei koya e curu, vakavuna me dua na cakacaka ni veivakalougatataki se dua na ivakarau ni kena kerei na veiqaravi vakayalo ni loma ni vale me tiko ga ena vakacegu.

Ni bera ni cakava e dua na ivakarau vakaoqo, e bibi me nanumi ni na duidui na ivakarau ni virika vatu kei na kena ibalebale ena nodra duidui na vanua vakavanua kei na nodra itovo na vanua yadudua. Sa gugumatua na veivosakitaki kei na kena vakadonui mai vei ira na vakaitavi ena vanua oya se na itovo vakavanua me baleta na kena vakayacori vakadodonu.

Fijian.text: O cei ko Ratu Sukuna?

English.text: Who was Ratu Sukuna?

Fijian.text:
Ratu Sir Lala Sukuna, whose full name was Ratu Sir Lala Sukuna Day, is one of Fiji's most revered national heroes. Born on 22 April 1888 and passing away on 30 May 1958, Ratu Sukuna was instrumental in shaping modern Fiji. He was not just a political leader but also held various roles throughout his life, including those of a scholar, soldier, statesman, and chief.

Educated in New Zealand and England, Ratu Sukuna was the first Fijian to study law, graduating from the University of Oxford. His education abroad provided him with a broad perspective, which he utilized to help navigate Fiji through the challenges of colonial rule and towards a more united and independent future.

During his lifetime, Ratu Sukuna worked tirelessly to promote unity among Fiji's diverse communities, including indigenous Fijians and Indo-Fijians. He played a significant role in establishing the modern Fijian administrative system and advocated for the preservation of Fijian land and cultural identity through the Native Land Trust Board (now the iTaukei Land Trust Board), which he helped to create in 1940. This institution was pivotal in safeguarding indigenous Fijian land for future generations.

Ratu Sukuna also served in various capacities, such as a member of the Legislative Council, the Executive Council, and was the first Speaker of the Fiji Legislative Council. His diplomatic skills and deep understanding of both Fijian and Western cultures allowed him to navigate the complex issues of his time effectively.

Ratu Sukuna's legacy is remembered and honored in Fiji through Ratu Sukuna Day, which was celebrated annually on the last Monday of May until 2010, when the public holiday was abolished. Despite this, his contributions to Fijian society, his vision for a united Fiji, and his efforts to balance tradition with modernity live on as a key part of the nation's collective memory and identity.

Fijian.text: O iko na cakava vakacava na kakana ka daukilai kina nida kai Viti o ya na rourou vakautona?

English.text: How would you make the Fijian delicacy of 'rourou vakautona' that is unique to your Fijian culture?

Fijian.text:
Na rourou vakautona e dua na kakana vakavanua ni Viti ka masi sara na kena tatadra ga na dinau (rourou) kei na ika se na vakautona (kena kena saurara nai vovo ni niu). Na vakarautaki ni kakana oqo e rawa ni vakaraitaki ena veika e muri:

### Vakavinavinaka ni Veika e Gadrevi:

- **Dinau (Taro Leaves)**: 10-15 na drau ni dinau, vaqara na drau lalai se lalaga me malumu vinaka.
- **Wai kamica ni Niu (Coconut Milk)**: 1-2 na bilo, v depending on na levu ni dinau kei na nomu vinakata na kena titobu.
- **Ika se vakautona (Optional)**: Vakarautaka na ika tauvu (vakadavori) se tini ni ika, rawa talega ni soli e dua na vakautona e vaka na tempe se tofu me kenadau veiganiti.
- **Masima kei na Vororo ni Vutu (Salt and Grated Ginger)**: Me vakarautaki me vaka na via kania.
- **Wai (Water)**: Me veiraurau

### Veika e cakava:

1. **Vakasavasavataka na Dinau**: Vakasavasavataki vakavinaka na drau ni dinau ena wai, oti qai vagalalataka, oka kina na kena taviraka se tavu.

2. **Vakarautaki ni Vakautona kei na Coconut Milk**: Vakavakarau na wai kamica ni niu, ka vakarautaka talega na vakautona se na ika kemuni vinakata.

3. **Vakarautaka na Rourou**: Viritaka yani na drau ni dinau e na dua na kuro lalai ka vota vata kei na lailai na masima kei na vororo ni vutu. Oti, kureitaka na dinau me tabaki vinaka e loma ni kuro.

4. **Curu ika se vakautona**: Kevaka o vakayagataka na ika se vakautona, dara sara ena loma ni drau ni dinau qai bulia me bale vakavinaka.

5. **Vakatawa ni Coconut Milk**: Waki na wai kamica ni niu ena delana, vakaraici me kakua ni sivia na levu ni wai ni niu me qai rawa ni tatadi vinaka na rourou.

6. **Vakasaqaqara ena Kuro se Lovo**: Vakarautaka na kuro ena dela ni stove ka vakasaqara tiko ena katakata lailai me rauta na 30 na miniti, se vakayagataka na ivakarau vakavanua ni lovo me ra sivia kina na kena tatadra.

7. **Raica na Kena Done**: Ni oti na 30 na miniti, raica se sa malumu vinaka na dinau ka sa vovodea na kena tatadra. Me kua ni vakasaqai vakasivia me qai kakua ni malai.

8. **Vakarau me Served**: Vakarautaki me served ni se katakata, e vinaka me vakayagataki vata kei na madrai, rice, se boiled cassava/tavioka.

Nodra i tovo na vakailesilesi e rawa ni duidui kei na veivanua e Viti, ia na veika e vakamacalataki e cake e dua na ivakarau vouvakataki ni kena vakarautaki. Vakayagataka na nomu vakatulewa ena kena vakayacori na veisau me salavata kei na nomu vinakata kei na veika e tu vei iko.

Fijian.text:
Na tabua, e mareqeti vakalevu ena vanua ni Pasifika, vakabibi e Viti, baleta e tautauvata kei na veiwekani, veidokai, kei na veilomani. E kilai na tabua me dua na ka vakamareqeti ka yaga vakalevu ka vakayagataki ena solevu duidui, me vaka na veivakamau, veisureti, veivosoti, kei na veigauna e gadrevi kina na veivakadonui se veirogoci.

Na tabua e dua na bati ni tani levu sa viviraki ka masima, ka dau vakayagataki me isoro se iloloma e na gauna ni veiqaravi vakavanua e Viti kei na veiyanuyanu e lomani koya. Na nona ivakarau raraba ena solevu vakavanua e vakaraitaka na ivakatakilakila ni veidokai kei na iyau, ka sa dau nanumi me dua na ka ni yalayala kei na veiwekani e sa na sega ni mudu rawa.

Na vuna e mareqeti kina tiko ga na tabua:

1. **Ivakatakarakara ni Vanua kei na Kawa Bula**: Na tabua e dau vakaraitaki me ivakatakarakara ni nodra bula, itovo, kei na itukutuku makawa na kai Pasifika. E dau vakamareqeti tiko me vaka e dua na kena ivakaraitaki ni nodra itovo vaka-Viti kei na nodra ivakarau ni bula.

2. **Veitikina Vakavanua (Cultural Significance)**: E vakatakarakarataka na veiwekani vakavanua, na veidokai, kei na dina ena maliwa ni veitikotiko kei na vanua. Ena so na gauna, e vakayagataki me ivakatakilakila ni veiyalayalati se nona vakaitavi o e dua ena dua na soqo vakaturaga.

Educated in Fiji, New Zealand, and the United Kingdom, Ratu Mara was highly educated and possessed a deep understanding of both traditional Fijian culture and Western political systems. He served as Fiji's first Prime Minister from 1970, when Fiji gained independence, until 1992, and again from 1993 to 1997. He was also appointed as President of Fiji, serving from 1993 to 2000. His tenure was not without challenges, including racial tensions, coups, and political instability, particularly regarding the rights and roles of the Indo-Fijian community.

Ratu Mara was knighted by Queen Elizabeth II, reflecting his status and the respect he earned both domestically and internationally. His leadership style, characterized by a commitment to dialogue and reconciliation, played a significant role in shaping Fiji's post-colonial identity and its place in the Pacific region.

Despite his efforts, Fiji has faced ongoing political challenges, including coups in 1987, 2000, and 2006, which have often been racially motivated or exacerbated by ethnic tensions. Perioada sa ca prim-ministru a fost marcată de încercări de reformă constituțională și economică, dar și de tensiuni etnice continue. În 1997, a jucat un rol cheie în crearea unei noi constituții care încerca să rezolve unele dintre aceste tensiuni, oferind mai multă reprezentare politică indo-fijianilor, deși aceasta nu a rezolvat complet problemele de bază.

După ce a părăsit funcția de prim-ministru, Rabuka a rămas activ în politică și în viața publică din Fiji, implicându-se în diverse roluri și adesea comentând afacerile politice și sociale ale națiunii. A avut perioade în care a fost mai puțin vizibil în politica de prim-plan, dar a continuat să-și exprime opiniile și să participe la dialogul național.

Mai recent, Rabuka și-a anunțat intenția de a reveni în viața politică activă, ocupându-se de probleme precum guvernanța, egalitatea etnică și reconcilierea națională. Acest lucru reflectă cariera sa lungă și complexă, care cuprinde roluri de leadership militar, prim-ministru și consilier senior, precum și perioade de controversă și încercări de reabilitare a imaginii sale publice. Cu toate acestea, opiniile despre Rabuka sunt împărțite în Fiji, el fiind considerat de unii un erou național, în timp ce alții îl văd ca fiind responsabil de instabilitatea politică și tensiunile etnice din istoria recentă a Fijian.

Na Tabana Ni Qele Maroroi se na iTaukei Land Trust Board (TLTB) e dua na mataqali valenivolavola e tu mai Viti ka tauyavutaki ena 1940 me lewa ka maroroya na qele ni iTaukei. Na nona cakacaka bibi ena ruku ni lawa e vakayacori tiko ena Viti e vauca tu na veika oqo:

1. **Maroroi kei na Veitaqomaki ni Qele ni iTaukei:** Na TLTB e vukei ena veimaroroi kei na veitaqomaki ni qele ni iTaukei me kua ni yali se veisau na kena itaukei ka ra vakatauvatani kina na itaukei kei na veimataqali bisinisi se veika vakailavo.

2. **Veivakadonui ena Veika vaQele:** Na TLTB e tuvai me ivakaraitaki ni veidigidigi ni lewa ena nodra vakayagataki na qele ni iTaukei, vakabibi vei ira na vinakata me ra volivoli se vakayagataka na qele ena veiyasai Viti. Oqo e okati kina na vunautaki kei na vakadonui ni vuku ni veikau, veivoli, se dua na ibulibuli vakabisinisi ena qele ni iTaukei.

3. **Veilesiyaki kei na iLavo Vakacavacava:** Na TLTB e vakarautaka talega na veilesiyaki kei na wase ni ilavo vakacavacava vei ira na itaukei ni qele ena nodra vakayagataki na nodra qele. Oqo e kenadau ni volivoli, volivolitaki, se veika vakailavo ka vakayacori ena qele ni iTaukei.

4. **Veivakasalataki kei na Vakasama Vakailavo:** Na TLTB e vukea na itaukei ni qele kei ira na vinakata me ra vakayagataka na qele ni iTaukei ena nodra soli vakasama vakailavo, vakasama ni veivakatorocaketaki, kei na vakatutu e na vuku ni veika vakailavo me ra na rawata mai na nodra qele.

5. **Veivakadodonutaki kei na Qaravi ni Veika Tata kei na Lewa:** Na TLTB e veivakadodonutaki talega ena vakatulewa kei na qaravi ni veika tata se leqa e rawa ni tubu cake mai na veika vakaqele, me vakadeitaka na dodonu ni itaukei ni qele kei na vakayagataki dodonu kei na qele.

Na TLTB e qarava na itavi bibi ena nodra sasaga na iTaukei me ra maroroya ka tara cake na kedra yaga mai na nodra qele, ia na nodra cakacaka e vukea talega ena veivakatorocaketaki ni vanua vakailavo kei na veiyasai Viti ena kena vakayagataki vakaturaga na qele ni iTaukei.
